<P>
CYCLONE KILLS AT LEAST 192 IN INDIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A raging cyclone that lashed two south Indian states has killed at least 192 
people over the past week, officials said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 About 54 people were killed by the cyclone and heavy rains in Tamil Nadu 
state, minister S.D. Somasundaram told lawmakers in the state Assembly. 
</P>
<P>
 In neighboring Andhra Pradesh, which shares the Bay of Bengal coastline, 138 
people died in collapsing buildings and flash floods that cut off roads and 
damaged irrigation channels. 
</P>
<P>
 Up to 33,000 huts, 10 buildings and 12 bridges in Tamil Nadu were destroyed, 
Somasundaram said, adding that the state government provided makeshift shelters 
for about 4,000 people made homeless by the storm. 
</P>
<P>
 Up to 40,000 were reported homeless in Andhra Pradesh. 
</P>
