<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dana Rudolph 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills, Senior 
</P>
<P>
 Tennis/Singles 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills struggled in the early part of the season, losing six of seven 
nonleague matches. Sunny Hills even lost to Sonora in the first round of league 
play, a shocking first for such four-year varsity players as Rudolph.But the 
Lancers turned it around last Tuesday, winning a share of the league title by 
beating Sonora, 10-8. Rudolph led the way, 6-0, 6-1, 6-0, and improved to 30-0 
in league play. She has lost six games in league. Rudolph, who hopes to attend 
Harvard, also won her second consecutive league title, beating teammate Barbie 
Bayless, 6-0, 6-4. She also beat Bayless in the final last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Cross-Country 
</P>
<P>
 Jessica Corbin 
</P>
<P>
 * Irvine, junior. Won the Sea View League title, finishing three miles in 16 
minutes 58 seconds to lead the Vaqueros to the team title. 
</P>
<P>
 Tennis 
</P>
<P>
 Sarah Denson 
</P>
<P>
 * Irvine, sophomore. Defeated Nina Vaughan of Corona del Mar, 6-4, 6-3, to win 
the Sea View League singles title for the second consecutive season. 
</P>
<P>
 Eleanor Luzano 
</P>
<P>
 * Rosary, sophomore. Defeated Judy Esmero of Westminster, 6-2, 7-5, to win the 
Golden West League singles title. 
</P>
<P>
 Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
 Kellie Alva 
</P>
<P>
 * Katella, junior. Had nine kills in a four-game victory over Cypress and 10 
aces in a three-game victory over Century as the Knights won a share of the 
Empire League title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
