<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joe Secoda 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia, Senior 
</P>
<P>
 Football/Quarterback 
</P>
<P>
 Secoda is much more than just Valencia's quarterback -- he kicks, he punts, he 
calls defensive signals from his position in the secondary. "He does just about 
everything for us," Valencia Coach Mike Marrujo said.That was clear Friday in a 
24-7 victory over Western that kept the Tigers in the running for the Orange 
League title. Secoda scored on a three-yard run, threw an eight-yard scoring 
pass, kicked a 34-yard field goal and three extra points. He also intercepted 
two passes -- and almost picked off a third -- giving him a county-leading nine 
this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 Charles Gatchell 
</P>
<P>
 * La Habra, senior. Finished second in the Freeway League finals, running 
three miles in 15 minutes 20 seconds and leading the Highlanders to their fifth 
consecutive team title. 
</P>
<P>
 Football 
</P>
<P>
 Jon Benzinger 
</P>
<P>
 * Newport Harbor, senior. Caught five passes for 152 yards and three 
touchdowns, including a 52-yard, game-winning score, in a 27-23 victory over 
Santa Margarita. 
</P>
<P>
 Charles Chatman 
</P>
<P>
 * Costa Mesa, senior. Rushed for 340 yards and two touchdowns in a 30-30 tie 
with University. 
</P>
<P>
 Water polo 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Stanley 
</P>
<P>
 * Esperanza, senior. Scored five goals in a 13-5 victory over Marina as the 
Aztecs won the Sunset League title and five in an 11-9 victory over Servite. 
</P>
