<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By By Jerry Hicks and Dennis McLellan and Mimi Ko 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TIMELY HELP: Ronald Reagan's Alzheimer's disclosure, to increase awareness, is 
already having a dramatic effect here. Monday morning, says Linda Scheck, 
director of the Alzheimer's Assn. of Orange County, "Our phones were going 
crazy." . . . The group's annual conference is Friday at the Pan Pacific Hotel 
in Anaheim, and the announcement has greatly increased interest in attendance. 
Adds Scheck: "It's kind of like a coming out, and we thank him for that." 
</P>
<P>
 NIXON & MAHONEY: Richard Nixon gets his name on a plaque at the new La Habra 
community center, at La Habra Boulevard and Euclid Street, where his old law 
office used to be. But some visitors at the dedication Monday (B2) wondered why 
the tiny patch of green at the corner is named Mahoney Park. . . . . Says City 
Manager Lee Risner: "It started as a joke and developed into a serious 
thought." Councilman William D. Mahoney had complained the corner was ugly, and 
needed grass and pretty flowers. Now it has. 
</P>
<P>
 TOUGH LOVE: With a book like "Sweet Revenge (How To Get Back at Men Who Have 
Wronged You)," readers may wonder if the authors, Devra Rossi of Newport Beach, 
right, and Elizabeth Wright of Fountain Valley, have ever been burned by the 
men in their lives. Answers Wright: "What woman hasn't?" . . . . The two 
discuss their book Wednesday on the Sally Jessie Raphael talk show (Channel 4, 
3 p.m.) One tip from the book: Get a picture of him naked and fax it to his 
office. 
</P>
<P>
 ADD LOVE: A different view on love comes late-night on Anaheim's KDOC-TV's, 
Channel 56, "The Love Channel," which features longtime radio personality Jim 
(the Poorman) Trenton of Newport Beach. The show includes medical experts and 
some celebrities, dispensing advice on romance, sex and health to young 
callers. . . . This month, the show went national: It's been picked up by 
Network One, a 24-hour cable satellite network. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Top of Today's News is on A2 By Jerry Hicks and Dennis McLellan and Mimi 
Ko 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
