</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks residents interested in trees, traffic, planning or disabled 
access can apply for openings on four city committees.All applications are due 
by the end of December, and all appointments carry four-year terms. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Planning Commission, which rules on development issues and coordinates 
the city's long-term growth, has three vacancies. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Traffic and Transportation Advisory Commission, which recommends ways to 
smooth transit throughout the city, has four vacancies. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Tree and Landscape Advisory Board, which studies the city's landscape 
policies, has three vacancies. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Disabled Access Appeals and Advisory Board, which seeks to ensure that 
construction complies with federal and state rules, has three vacancies. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call City Clerk Nancy Dillon at 449-2151. STEPHANIE SIMON 
