<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Roaming into downtown Orange is a little like stepping back in time. 
</P>
<P>
 The Old Towne Plaza is home to 46 antique shops that radiate from the city's 
famous traffic circle at Glassell Street and Chapman Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The 47th shop is due to open next month. 
</P>
<P>
 The ambience of the historic plaza, which was founded in 1876, creates a nice 
setting for an antique district, according to David Connelly of the Old Towne 
Antique Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 The 70- and 80-year-old buildings are perfectly designed for small antique 
shops, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The antique boom began in 1972 when Marty Burns opened her shop on Glassell 
called Marty's Things. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Need help selecting a university after attending community college? 
</P>
<P>
 Representatives from more than 60 colleges and universities will be at 
Saddleback College from 9:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. as part of college/university 
transfer day. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will be at the upper campus quad. Students are invited to pick up 
information from both public and private schools. Saddleback College is at 
28000 Marguerite Parkway in Mission Viejo. Information: (714) 582-4494. 
</P>
