<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; CITY IS ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Applications are being accepted from organizations and agencies for Community 
Development Block Grants. 
</P>
<P>
 The city has participated in this program for the past 20 years and receives 
about $1.6 million a year, said Carol Runzel, city assistant project manager. 
</P>
<P>
 Federal guidelines allow the city to spend 20% of the grant money for 
administration and 55% toward projects and programs by the public and private 
sectors, Runzel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Public and social services projects, such as programs that assist the 
homeless, seniors and the needy and those that provide child care for 
low-income individuals, receive 15% of the grant money. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant money can also be used for projects to improve neighborhoods and to meet 
an urgent community development needs. 
</P>
<P>
 The remaining 10% of grant money will be set aside as contingency reserves, 
Runzel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available at the Economic Development Department at City 
Hall, 2000 Main St. The deadline is Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 536-5583.DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
