<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; NEW RESTROOMS OKD FOR PLAZA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Plaza Park, at the corner of Chestnut Street and Thompson Boulevard, should be 
improved with new restrooms and possibly a gazebo, the Ventura City Council 
decided Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The council requested bids on the construction project, estimating that the 
city would pay about $170,000 to replace old restrooms and to remove a nearby 
concrete structure once used as restrooms but now overgrown with dirt and 
weeds. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura has also received nearly $50,000 in federal funds to pay about half 
the estimated $100,000 cost of the gazebo, city officials said. But the city 
would construct the gazebo only if there is enough money left from the restroom 
project, or if other funds are found for it in other accounts, the council 
decided. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction of the restrooms is expected to start in late December. CONSTANCE 
SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
