<HEADLINE>
<P>
ERRONEOUS REPORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I believe that erroneous information is being circulated about a company 
called The Worm Concern.  
</P>
<P>
 I have been a customer of this odd but interesting effort to use regenerative 
materials for the last 10 years.Thanks to its superior products (compost and 
worms) I have had a beautiful and abundant garden for years. 
</P>
<P>
 I have visited The Worm Concern on many occasions and have often been 
accompanied by my children. We have always enjoyed these visits and none of us 
has ever detected any foul odors or seen any vermin (unlike garbage dumps, 
landfills, etc., compost must be clean to develop properly because it must be 
exposed to air). 
</P>
<P>
 In search of composting materials I have also visited several horse stables, 
where I have consistently noticed odors, flies and other environmentally 
adverse conditions. 
</P>
<P>
 I suggest that before anybody judges The Worm Concern that they visit the farm 
and see for themselves. 
</P>
<P>
 GERALD D. RAPHAEL 
</P>
<P>
 Encino 
</P>
