<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; FIRE DEPARTMENT JOINS EMERGENCY TASK FORCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has authorized the Fire Department to join a task force that 
helps perform rescues during major emergencies and disasters. 
</P>
<P>
 The Urban Search and Rescue task force is made up of representatives from 
federal, state, county and local agencies. Members have been called to such 
emergencies as the 1989 San Francisco earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire Chief Vincent Bonacker said last week that Fire Department employees have 
participated in the task force's work for three years. He called on the city to 
formalize its participation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
