<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: IRVINE; TEEN HITS TRUCK, DIES ON SANTA ANA FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THAO HUA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 19-year-old man died Monday morning after losing control of his vehicle on 
the Santa Ana Freeway and swerving into a truck, the California Highway Patrol 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 John Michael McGlone of Laguna Hills was pronounced dead at the scene after 
the left side of his car "hit the front wheel of a big-rig truck and went under 
the rear trailer," CHP Officer Michael Lundquist said. 
</P>
<P>
 The rear wheels of the truck "went over the top of the car," crushing the left 
side, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man was heading south on the freeway north of Lake Forest Drive at 9:45 
a.m. when he apparently lost control, Lundquist said. 
</P>
<P>
 No other injuries were reported. The truck driver, who was in the inside lane 
going about 55 m.p.h., was not cited, Lundquist said. 
</P>
<P>
 Maria Sabol, a spokeswoman for the Orange County Fire Department, said there 
was evidence that a fire had broken out after the collision, possibly due to a 
gasoline spill. But it was under control by the time the firefighters arrived, 
she said. THAO HUA 
</P>
</TEXT>
