<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: WINNETKA; FIREFIGHTER HURT, 5 INJURED IN BLAZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Los Angeles firefighter was in good condition Monday after receiving 
second-degree burns while battling a house fire that caused $100,000 in damage 
and left a family of five homeless, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The firefighter, whose name was not released pending notification of 
relatives, was burned on the neck. He was taken to Northridge Hospital Medical 
Center, Fire Department spokesman Jim Wells said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire broke out Sunday night about 8 p.m. at 20220 Arminta St., Wells said, 
and by the time firefighters arrived, they found the one-story family dwelling 
engulfed with flames. The family is believed to be staying with relatives. The 
cause of the blaze is unknown. TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
