<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SOUTH COUNTY; SENIOR CITIZEN DRIVING COURSES SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An opportunity for senior citizens to improve their driving skills and qualify 
for insurance discounts is available through driving courses that will be held 
this month throughout South County. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-day course focuses on helping senior citizens compensate for slowing 
reflexes and vision problems, and it informs participants about Department of 
Motor Vehicles driving regulations. 
</P>
<P>
 Called 55 Alive, the program is sponsored by the American Assn. of Retired 
Persons, and participants must be at least age 50. The course costs $8, and 
registration in advance is required. 
</P>
<P>
 When the eight-hour course is completed, senior citizens are given a 
certificate that can be sent to insurance companies for good-driver discounts. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in signing up must contact the facility where the class is 
being held. Classes in South County this month are scheduled for: 
</P>
<P>
 * Saturday and Nov. 19 from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. at the Laguna Beach Senior Center 
in Lang Park at 384 Legion St. For more information, call (714) 497-2441. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nov. 14 and 15 from 9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the San Clemente Senior Citizen 
Center, 242 Avenida del Mar. For more information, call (714) 498-3322. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nov. 15 and 16 from 8 a.m. to noon at Glendale Federal Bank, 24221 Calle de 
la Louisa, Laguna Hills. For more information, call (714) 768-7771. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nov. 28 and 29 from 8 a.m. to noon at the Norman P. Murray Community and 
Senior Center, 24932 Oso Viejo Road, in Mission Viejo. For more information, 
call (714) 470-3062. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
