<P>
GARDENER DENIES SEXUALLY ABUSING DOG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANN W. O'NEILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Northridge gardener pleaded not guilty in Van Nuys Municipal Court on Monday 
to charges he sexually abused a German shepherd named Bubu. 
</P>
<P>
 Arturo Mathias, 46, returns to court Dec. 12 for further hearings in a case in 
which he has been charged with five counts of animal abuse and five counts of 
sexually assaulting an animal, Deputy City Atty.Don Cocek said. 
</P>
<P>
 According to Cocek, Mathias appeared every Monday at 9 a.m. at the Van Nuys 
apartment complex where Bubu, now about 18 months old, lived with his owner. 
The prosecutor declined to identify the owner, who told police a roommate's 
mother told him in June that she had seen the gardener having sex with the dog. 
 
</P>
<P>
 The owner was disbelieving at first, but became suspicious when his roommate 
also said he had witnessed a sexual encounter between Bubu and the gardener. 
</P>
<P>
 Cocek said the owner witnessed the gardener's sexual activity with the 
100-pound male canine on five consecutive Mondays. On the advice of police, the 
owner videotaped a final incident, and a citizen's arrest was made on Oct. 24. 
</P>
<P>
 After the encounters with Bubu, Cocek said, the gardener would resume working. 
ANN W. O'NEILL 
</P>
