<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; INMATE ESCAPES FROM HONOR RANCHO WHILE WORKING 
ON CONSTRUCTION CREW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An inmate on a minimum-security work crew escaped from the Peter J. Pitchess 
Honor Rancho Monday afternoon, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Solis, 26, fled from a field next to the jail's welding shop while he 
was working on a construction crew about 2:15 p.m., said Deputy Brian Jones of 
the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Solis is described as Latino, 5 feet, 4 inches tall, 140 pounds with black 
hair and brown eyes, Jones said. He was last seen in his prison uniform, a 
light-green jumpsuit. 
