<P>
RAVELING TO GET OUT OF HOSPITAL TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LONNIE WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After nearly six weeks in the hospital following a near-fatal traffic 
accident, USC basketball Coach George Raveling is scheduled to be released from 
USC University Hospital today. 
</P>
<P>
 Raveling, who suffered nine broken ribs and a fractured pelvis and clavical on 
Sept. 25, will not return to coach the Trojans for at least six weeks. In his 
absence, USC assistants Charlie Parker and Jack Fertig will continue to coach 
the team. 
</P>
<P>
 USC, which will begin regular-season play Nov. 16 against New Mexico State in 
a preseason National Invitation tournament first-round game, lost to Australia 
on Monday night, 79-77, in an exhibition game at the Lyon Center. LONNIE WHITE 
</P>
