<P>
DISCUSSIONS HELD ON RAIDER MOVE TO BALTIMORE, PARTIAL SALE OF TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER and MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Peter Angelos, owner of the Baltimore Orioles, has had discussions with Raider 
owner Al Davis about moving the team to Baltimore and perhaps selling a piece 
of it to Maryland investors, according to a source close to the talks. 
</P>
<P>
 "All I can tell you is that there were discussions and it wasn't just a 
passing thing," said the source."They were obviously substantive discussions." 
</P>
<P>
 Although it has long been believed that Davis would never sell the club, these 
talks have involved the possibility of such a transaction. "It would strictly 
be a piece of the team," the source said. "Not all of it. Al would be reserving 
the right of operating the team." 
</P>
<P>
 A Raider official had no comment. STEVE SPRINGER and MIKE DiGIOVANNA 
