<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP WATER POLO PAIRINGS; EL TORO'S STREAK MIGHT END AT THE HANDS OF VILLA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Toro, which has won 22 consecutive water polo playoff games, might have a 
tough time reaching 23. In the most intriguing matchup of the Southern Section 
Division I playoffs announced Monday, the Chargers play Villa Park Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro has won the last two Division I titles. The Chargers won Division 3-A 
titles in 1988, '89 and '90, but missed the playoffs in '91. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park also has something extra to play for -- Coach Jeff Erlich's 400th 
career victory. Ehrlich is 399-137 in 21 seasons at the school. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park (20-7) and El Toro (15-11) split two games this season, each 
winning, 8-5. Villa Park was ranked No. 6 in the final Division I poll and El 
Toro No. 8. The game will be played at a site to be determined by Villa Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Three Orange County teams received top seedings: Corona del Mar (21-4) in 
Division I, Esperanza (20-6) in Division II and Brea-Olinda (22-4) in Division 
VI. 
</P>
<P>
 Sea View League champion Corona del Mar will play host to Lakewood (9-12), the 
third-place team from the Moore League, Thursday. Second-seeded San Clemente 
(24-2) plays host to Sherman Oaks Notre Dame (17-8), an at-large team from the 
Mission League. No. 4 Foothill (20-5) will play host to Mission Viejo (13-13). 
</P>
<P>
 In the all-Orange County Division II, Servite (18-9) is seeded second, Costa 
Mesa (21-5) is seeded third and La Habra (15-4) fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback (16-6), which will play at La Habra Friday, is making its first 
playoff appearance since 1980. 
</P>
<P>
 Wild-card games in Division II and VI are today and the first round is Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The pairings (games 3:15 p.m. unless noted): 
</P>
<P>
