<P>
PREP VOLLEYBALL PAIRINGS; SUNSET LEAGUE'S MARINA SHUT OUT OF PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marina girls' volleyball Coach Jason Bilbruck found out what is worse than a 
bad draw for the Southern Section playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the Vikings finished tied for third in the Sunset League, arguably 
one of the strongest leagues in the section, they weren't invited to the 
playoffs, which begin today. The Vikings (10-7) tied Esperanza (7-7) for third, 
splitting their head-to-head matches. But Esperanza won the tie-breaker because 
it defeated Marina in four games. Marina defeated Esperanza in five. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's in our league constitution that we don't play a playoff match for 
third-place ties," Bilbruck said. "That's one of the first things I'll bring up 
at our league meeting." 
</P>
<P>
 If Marina was playing in Division II, it could have petitioned for one of the 
two at-large berths. But there were no at-large berths available in Division I. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor (21-1), led by Misty May and Melissa Schutz, is the top-seeded 
team in Division I. Manhattan Beach Mira Costa (17-0) is seeded second, Laguna 
