<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY & TELECOMMUNICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AT&T Settles Suit by Bell Atlantic and Nynex: AT&T Corp. has settled an 
antitrust lawsuit with Bell Atlantic Corp. and Nynex Corp. over the telephone 
giant's takeover of McCaw Cellular Communications Inc., the companies 
said.AT&T, which was already the nation's largest supplier of wireless 
equipment, acquired McCaw for $11.5 billion in September, making it the 
nation's biggest provider of wireless services as well. Bell Atlantic and Nynex 
complained that AT&T was both the sole supplier of wireless equipment to them 
and a mighty competitor in providing mobile-calling services. The three agreed 
on a cost-sharing formula to ensure that AT&T wireless network equipment will 
be compatible with other manufacturers' equipment -- a concept known as "open 
interface." 
</P>
