EXECUTIVE SUITE: DAN KLORES TO OPEN L.A. OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dan Klores Associates, a New York-based public relations firm, is opening Dan 
Klores Entertainment in Los Angeles. The office will be headed by Hayley 
Sumner, who has represented such Klores clients as Garry Shandling, Jay Leno 
and Howard Stern. 
</P>
<P>
 In her new position, Sumner will spearhead the company's moves into marketing 
and promotions, in addition to public relations. She currently serves as 
executive vice president of Klores. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dana Miller, co-chairman of Entertainment Radio Networks, 
</P>
<P>
 has been named board chair of AIDS Project Los Angeles, succeeding producer 
Steve Tisch. 
</P>
<P>
 * Darcie Denkert was named executive vice president of business affairs at 
Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 * Robin Berlin was named vice president of talent and specials at MTV: Music 
Television. 
</P>
<P>
 * Castle Rock Pictures has named Curtis Burch vice president of production. 
</P>
<P>
 * Samuel Goldwyn Co. has named Neil Dick vice president of advertising. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jay Poyner was named president and chief operating officer of Animagic 
Entertainment Group. Leonard Gruenberg was named special adviser. 
</P>
