<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: MARTIN LAWRENCE REDUCES 3RD-QUARTER LOSS FROM '93 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Martin Lawrence Ltd. Editions Inc., a Van Nuys artwork retailer, said it 
narrowed its loss to $816,000 from $1.3 million for the third quarter that 
ended Sept. 30, compared to the same period last year.Third-quarter revenue was 
$4.36 million, down 6% from $4.64 million the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, the company's loss was $3.1 million, compared to $5.4 
million in the first nine months last year. Revenue for the nine months was 
$12.9 million, down slightly from $13.2 million in the same period last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said its loss decreased in the third quarter due to cuts in 
administrative and other costs. In other news, the company said it opened its 
first factory outlet store in September in Milpitas, Calif., and will consider 
opening more factory outlets if that store proves successful. 
</P>
