<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: INCOMNET POSTS RECORD QUARTERLY SALES, EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Incomnet Inc., a Woodland Hills telecommunications company, reported its 
fourth consecutive quarter of record sales and earnings in the third quarter 
that ended Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 The company posted profit of $1.06 million in the third quarter, compared with 
a year-earlier loss of $68,118.Revenues surged to $12.8 million from $2.7 
million in the third quarter of 1993. The company said it gained more revenue 
in the third quarter than in all of last year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first nine months of the year, Incomnet reported net income of $2.63 
million on sales of $30.7 million, compared with a year-earlier loss of $1.27 
million on sales of $6.23 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the improved results to continued sales growth in its 
National Telephone & Communications Inc. unit, a subsidiary that buys excess 
capacity on fiber-optic cable lines from major telephone companies, then sells 
it at discount prices through a network of independent salespeople. 
</P>
<P>
 Incomnet said its National Telephone unit has seen a dramatic expansion of its 
customer base. 
</P>
</TEXT>
