REGIONAL EARNINGS: IHOP POSTS RECORD EARNINGS IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 IHOP Corp., the Glendale developer and operator of pancake restaurants, said 
it had record earnings of $3.78 million for the third quarter that ended Sept. 
30, up 9% from $3.46 million last year. Sales for the quarter were $37.3 
million, down 2% from $38.2 million the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, the company said earnings were $9.73 million, up 55% from 
$6.2 million in the first nine months last year. Revenues for same period were 
$107.2 million, up 3% from $103.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said the results for the nine-month period were attributable to 
healthy patronage at both company-owned and franchised restaurants, and a 
decline in the number of new franchise agreements, which dampened sales 
somewhat compared with last year. Twenty-three IHOP restaurants were franchised 
last year compared with 14 this year. 
</P>
<P>
 IHOP opened eight new restaurants in the third quarter, bringing the total 
number opened this year to 28. 
</P>
