<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PREMIERE RADIO PROFIT SURGES TO $458,562 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Premiere Radio Networks Inc., a Sherman Oaks producer of syndicated radio 
programming, said its third-quarter earnings rose sharply as several recent 
acquisitions contributed to its bottom line. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months ended Sept. 30, Premiere had a profit of $458,562, up from 
$25,249 in net income a year before. Revenue grew to $4.17 million, a 38% 
increase from $3.03 million. 
</P>
<P>
 In the recent nine-month period, Premiere earned $1.83 million, in contrast 
with a year-earlier loss of $300,594. Revenue rose 58%, to $12 million from 
$7.58 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the recent acquisitions contributing to Premiere's improved results are 
radio programs it bought from Olympia Networks of Missouri Inc. and its 
purchase of Mediabase Research Corp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
