</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gov. Steve Merrill has written a letter of apology to a Chicago woman who was 
refused lodging at three motels in Manchester because she carried no ID showing 
her name. 
</P>
<P>
 The Econo Lodge, Howard Johnson and the Queen City Motor Inn refused to rent 
Linda Friedberg a room Sept. 7, though she had $1,000 in cash. All three said 
they were protecting the safety of the business and guests. 
</P>
<P>
 Friedberg said she will never visit New Hampshire again. "I've never met 
people who had such an attitude about them. There was no compassion in them," 
